industries to ensure appropriate measures are timely vetted and resolved,=
=0F"=20
she said.

Commissioner Harold W. Furchtgott-Roth dissented from the FCC=0F's decision=
,=20
saying it was =0F"premature=0F" to address the issue of cable interactive T=
V=20
services.  =0F"While the item is framed as a notice of inquiry, it is no le=
ss=20
damaging to raise the specter of government regulation. . .for services tha=
t=20
are still in their gestational period.=0F"  He said he had =0F"serious=20
