New Entrants Will Prolong IXC Price Wars, Analysts Say

The financial future of interexchange carriers (IXCs) continues to be cloud=
ed=20
by downward pressure on rates for voice long distance services, financial=
=20
analysts say.  That pressure will intensify=0F-and will begin to affect dat=
a=20
service, too=0F-as new entrants like Global Crossing Ltd. and Level 3=20
Communications, Inc., finish building networks and Bell companies gain=20
permission to offer in-region interLATA (local access and transport area)=
