their next-generation networks cost less to run than older networks, Mr.=20
Reingold said Friday, Jan. 19, during a conference call with clients.

Rosemarie Kalinowski, an analyst for the credit-rating agency Standard & Po=
or=0F'
s, agreed that pressure would intensify on long distance carriers. =20

Incumbents like AT&T Corp. and WorldCom, Inc., are building new Internet=20
protocol networks, she noted.  But it=0F's unclear whether those networks w=
ill=20
be finished in time to =0F"produce the cost efficiencies necessary to offse=
t the=20
pricing pressures and compete head-to-head with the new entrants,=0F" she s=
aid=20
during a teleconference earlier in the week.

Managers at incumbent IXCs apparently were in a state of denial or were=20
caught off guard by a steeper-than-expected decline in rates, Ms. Kalinowsk=
i=20
said.  They mistakenly thought they could correct the situation by cutting=
