rates=0F-and thereby reducing their profitability, she said.

Although Mr. Reingold advised investors to steer clear of most incumbent lo=
ng=20
distance carriers, he said he thought Sprint Corp. might increase in value=
=20
because of a potential merger with Qwest Communications International, Inc.=
 =20
He said he expected a Qwest-Sprint merger to be announced in the next 12=20
months.

Merger activity in general may increase under a Republican administration,=
=20
Mr. Reingold asserted.  But some combinations will remain difficult or=20
impossible because traditional antitrust laws and the Telecommunications Ac=
t=20
of 1996 will stand in the way, no matter who is in power, he said.  For=20
example, he said, recent speculation that a Bell company might buy WorldCom=
