The U.S. Telecom Association said the FCC=0F's proposal would increase the =
level=20
of detail required for the remaining six service-quality categories.  Despi=
te=20
the reduction in the number of categories, =0F"it is unclear whether the=20
reporting burden will be reduced,=0F" it said.

USTA also sharply disagreed with the FCC=0F's statement that its =0F"basic =
role in=20
service quality is to serve as an efficient clearinghouse for information.=
=0F" =20
USTA said that role was not statutorily defined and added that it=0F's =0F"=
unlikely=20
that ARMIS reports, even a streamlined version, will be a primary source of=
