service-quality data on the provisioning of DSL service.  =0F"Limited repor=
ting=20
obligations for DSL services by large ILECs and their data affiliates would=
=20
well serve the public with relevant service information, while reducing=20
carriers=0F' overall filing burden as compared to the current ARMIS=20
obligations,=0F" it said.=20

Retaining the current reporting requirements would bring =0F"no material ad=
verse=20
consequences,=0F" AT&T Corp. said.  Meeting those obligations is not a=20
significant burden for ILECs, it said.  =0F"The systems seeded to generate =
the=20
ARMIS data are already established and were funded by captive ratepayers=20
years ago,=0F" AT&T added.  =0F"In fact, introducing different reporting=20
requirements may be more costly for the ILECs than maintaining the current=
=20
ones, because any changes to current requirements will necessitate systems=
