changes,=0F" AT&T concluded.

Interexchange carriers (IXCs) don=0F't have =0F"bargaining power to obtain=
=20
good-quality access service provisioning from ILECs,=0F" WorldCom Corp. sai=
d. =20
ARMIS data shows a =0F"steady decline=0F" in service quality from ILECs ove=
r the=20
past two years, showing that =0F"ILECs are engaged in precisely the type of=
=20
behavior that the service-quality reports are intended to reveal:  maximizi=
ng=20
earnings by reducing service quality,=0F" it said.

