Regulatory & Government Affairs

The FCC has accepted the applications of three prospective bidders for its=
=20
auction of eight licenses in the =0F"guard bands=0F" surrounding public saf=
ety=20
spectrum in the 700 megahertz frequencies.  The sale is scheduled to begin=
=20
Feb. 13.  The Form 175 applications of Nextel Spectrum Acquisition Corp.,=
=20
Harbor Wireless LLC, and Pegasus Guard Band LLC have been accepted.  The=20
applications of Access Spectrum LLC and PTPMS II Communications LLC are=20
incomplete because of invalid attachments, the agency said.  Those two=20
applicants must correct the minor deficiencies and submit the require=20
up-front payments by Jan. 26. in order to participate in the auction. =20
Companies whose applications have been accepted also must submit up-front=
=20
payments by that time.  The licenses involved went unsold at an auction in=
=20
September 2000.

The Commercial Wireless Division of the FCC=0F's Wireless Telecommunication=
s=20
Bureau has extended the time to comment on the Real Access Alliance=0F's mo=
tion=20
for a stay of certain rules on access to multitenant buildings (TR, Jan.=20
15).  The division said comments now will be due Jan. 26 in Wireless=20
Telecommunications docket 99-217 and Common Carrier dockets 96-98 and 88-57=
. =20
The Wireless Communications Association International had requested the=20
extension.

The FCC=0F's Wireless Telecommunications Bureau is seeking comments on two=
=20
requests for waivers of the Commission=0F's construction rules governing 90=
0=20
megahertz band licensees.  The rules require major trading area (MTA)=20
licensees to provide coverage to at least two-thirds of their population=20
within five years of being granted a license.  Neoworld License Holdings,=
